92. During the Time of the Emperors, the _Romans_ seem to have been more given to Intrigues and Gallantry than the _English_ are at present: And the Women of Condition, in order to retain their Lovers, endeavour'd to fix a Name of Reproach on those, who were addicted to wenching and low Amours. They were call'd _Ancillarioli_. See Seneca de Beneficiis. Lib. I. Cap. 9. See also Martial, Lib. 12. Epig. 58.

